headline: 3 Reasons to Sell MET and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Over the past six months, MetLife’s stock price fell to $77.79. Shareholders have lost 10.5% of their capital, which is disappointing considering the S&P 500 has climbed by 5.8%. This was partly due to its softer quarterly results and may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
